==English==
===Etymology===
From ''[[im-]]'' + Latin ''[[persona]]'' ‘person’ + ''[[-ate]]'', modelled on ''[[incorporate]]''.

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/ɪmˈpɜ:səneɪt/}}

===Verb===
{{en-verb|impersonat|ing}}

# (''transitive'') To manifest in corporeal form, or in one's own person or body.
# (''transitive'') To pretend to be (a different person), to assume the identity of.
#:''The [[conman]] managed to '''impersonate''' several executives.''

